page.title: 07Headland Surnames
page.content: {The Headland-H/pool By Jamie Comption {and By Ronald Bischof One afternoon we went from school to visit Northgate Library.We were going to find out which names were most common on the Headland,where some families have lived for generations. This is what we discovered when we looked through the Electors Roll. {Kennedy-26 adults,Boagey-24 adults, {Snowdon-17 adults,Pounder-15 adults, {Horsley-13 adults,Maiden-9 adults, {Skinner-5 adults. Ronnie Bischof discovered that his mum and dad were the only ones with that name in the whole North-Eastern area. That is probably because his grandfather came from Germany to settle in Britain.
